Program: Outlook
Title: Unsafe Death Penalty Convictions in the USA
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbr6v
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
How American students challenging death penalty convictions have caused many states to reconsider their stance on execution. Also, the Afghan boxer whose beard might prevent him taking part in the Olympics. And, why the element phosphorus can be used to either kill or cure us.